07/10/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Sunday (6 October), High Representative Paddy Ashdown appointed the director and two deputies of the Agency for Information and Security (SIPA), which is to serve as the Bosnian intelligence service. 
SIPA's first director will be Sredoje Novic, who served as Interior Minister under Milorad Dodik in Republika Srpska. 
His two deputies - Emir Bijedic and Dragan Lukac - come from the Bosnian and Croat communities respectively. 
All three have six-year terms and will rotate at the director level every two years. 
(HINA - 06/10/02)
